def process_data(data, filters=None, sort_by=None, aggregate=None):
    # Apply filters
    filtered = (
        [item for item in data if all(f(item) for f in filters)]
        if filters else data
    )

    # Apply sorting
    sorted_data = sorted(filtered, key=sort_by) if sort_by else filtered

    # Apply aggregation
    if not aggregate:
        return sorted_data

    aggregated = {}
    for item in sorted_data:
        key = aggregate(item)
        aggregated.setdefault(key, []).append(item)
    return aggregated
